🔴 P0 — Critical Missing Pieces

1. Streaming Provider Abstraction — Omo-Koda2's `ProviderRegistry::think()` returns a plain `String`. Claw-code has full SSE streaming with `TokenEvent` enum (Token, ToolUseStart, ToolUseInput, ToolUseEnd, Done). This is needed for real-time UX and parallel tool execution.

2. Permission System (Deny-First) — Omo-Koda2 only has a simple tier check (`if !self.tools.is_allowed(&tool, tier)`). It needs Claw-code's `PermissionPolicy` with `DenyRule` precedence, `PermissionMode` (ReadOnly/WorkspaceWrite/Prompt/Allow), and interactive `PermissionPrompter`.

3. Bash Validation (18 Submodules) — Omo-Koda2 has basic sandboxing but no command validation. Claw-code's `bash_validation.rs` has: `readOnlyValidation`, `destructiveCommandWarning`, `modeValidation`, `sedValidation`, `pathValidation`, `commandSemantics`.

4. Safety Stack (7-Layer Defense) — This is architectural, not from Claw-code directly. Omo-Koda2 needs defense-in-depth: ToolPrefilter → DenyFirstRules → PermissionModeLayer → AutoModeClassifier → ShellSandboxLayer → NoResumeRestoreLayer → HookInterceptorLayer.

